description:
Responsibilities：

Handle the accounting entries of the company and its subsidiaries and to develop and improve the accounting, financial, auditing and internal control management systems of the Company;
Submit FRR and annual audited financial statements to SFC;
Prepare and monitor enforcement of annual budget, monthly financial statements and consolidation financial statements;
Prepare financial analysis, internal management reports and all financial analysis reports;
Handle tax issues, accounts receivables and payables, client fund deposit and withdrawal, and annual auditing;
Responsible for fund management, monitor liquid capital position;
Assist with Investment services department to jointly monitor the credit status of margin clients.
Liaise with tax authority, auditors, banks and SFC on finance related matters.

Requirements:

Bachelor’s Degree or above in accounting and finance, qualified accountant or members;
3-4 years accounting and finance relevant experiences in investment banks or securities brokerage firms, familiar with accounting rules and regulations of securities business, familiar with accounting systems and back office system;
Have a high level of responsibility and good communication and coordination skills, strong sense of moral values, pay attention to details, have a good team spirit and professional attitude.
We offer 5-day work week and competitive remuneration package to qualified candidates. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" and submit your resume with current and expected salary .Please visit our company’s website: https://www.tiandafinancial.com to know more about us.

All information provided by applicants will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Responsibilities:


Manage the preparation of regular management reports and analyses, forecast and budget reports;
Work closely with the external advisers for the statutory reporting and ensure compliance with HK listing rules and other related requirements;
Set up accounting report packages and internal policies and procedures;
Assist Group Financial Controller in performing treasury functions and ad hoc projects or assignments;
Handle tax computation matters, statutory and tax filings;
Manage and develop subordinates in a wide range of functions.
Job Requirements:


Degree holder or above in Accounting/Finance or related discipline;
CPA or equivalent professional qualifications;
Minimum10 years working experience in Hong Kong listed companies, and big 4 accounting firms background preferred;
Familiar with HK and PRC accounting and tax practices, solid experience in group consolidation and SEHK regulatory requirements
Good communication and interpersonal skills, demonstrated performance in people leadership, able to motivate teams to perform effectively and efficiently and handle multi-tasks with tight deadlines;
Strong analytical and business sense, strong report writing and presentation skills;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua);
Immediate available is highly preferred.
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Assistant Accounting Manager.

We offer attractive package including 5-day work and fringe benefit to the right candidate. Interested candidates please apply with full resume stating present & expected salary and date available by e-mail.


