Responsibilities:

Report to Financial Controller and supervise the day to day operations of a team of accounting staff;
Managing month-end closing, group consolidation, and financial analysis, statutory reporting, forecasting, management reporting;
Ensuring internal controls and compliance with accounting and legislative requirements;
Assist with tax computation annually; dealing with annual statutory audit, external and internal auditors;
Coordinate with the subsidiaries and group companies in all financial matters;
Assist in overseeing the internal control of the group;
Implement and enforce finance policies and procedures, tight controls and reporting system;
Ad hoc projects from time to time.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Accounting or related disciplines;
8 years experience in finance and accounting;
Relevant experience in listed company is required;
In-depth knowledge in HK & PRC compliance regulations in such areas as tax and the HK Stock Exchange Listing Rules.
Professional qualification of HKICPA, ACCA or equivalent;
Fluent/Native in Putonghua and is a MUST. ;
Self-initiative detail-minded, able to work under pressure and tight deadline.
We offer an attractive remuneration package to the right applicants. Interested parties, please send your full resume with current and expected salary and availability by clicking “Apply Now”.

Personal data collected will be treated in strict confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.

Our client is a leading financial services company in Hong Kong. 



Responsibilities:

Handling daily accounting operations including AR/AP, general journal entries, bills and payments, bank reconciliation;
Handle full set of accounts including bank reconciliation, general ledger, fixed assets register, prepayment, accruals and month-end closing and etc;
Prepare monthly management accounts with accounting schedules and reconciliations on timely basis, including trust reconciliation against client assets;
Liaise with external auditor and tax representatives for the preparation of statutory financial reports and tax filing.
Perform ad-hoc assignments as required

Requirements:

Degree holder in Accounting, Finance or related discipline;
Around 1-3 years accounting experience for the financial services sector;
Highly independent, self-motivated, enthusiastic, capable to meet deadline and work under pressure
Good command of written and spoken Chinese, English and Mandarin;
Good interpersonal and communications skills;
Self-motivated, detail oriented, strong sense of responsibility and multi-tasked

Please feel free to send your updated profile together with your salary information to resume(at)ruikezixun.com to have a further discussion.

Responsibilities:


Involve in a wide range of international corporate finance transactions (including M&A, restructuring);
Fully participate in the financial and tax due diligence and the execution processes;
Play a key role in the investment project team;
Assist in preparation of accounting schedules for year-end audit;
Perform analytical and business analysis for management;
Handle ad hoc financial reports and projects

 Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in Accounting / Finance or an internationally recognized accounting qualification;
Minimum 4 years’ relevant experience, including 3 years experience gained in Big 4 / sizable listed companies;
Solid corporate finance experience in M&A transactions would be advantageous;
Working knowledge in the HK Listing Rules is required;
Excellent understanding of the PRC accounting rules and regulation;
Strong analytical, reporting and problem solving skills;
Result oriented and able to work under tight deadlines;
Self-motivated, responsible, a good team player and willing to travel;
Proficiency in computer application software;
Fluent communication skills in English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred.

*Candidates with less experience will be considered as Assistant Finance Manager.

We offer 5-day work, attractive salary package and other fringe benefits to the right candidate. 

Interested parties please send your detailed resume in MS Word format with your present and expected salary to us. 

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and will be treated only for employment related purpose.

The candidate will be in charge of completing various assignments either independently or as a team while reporting to the director in areas such as audit, accountancy and tax compliance including but not limited to the preparation of financial statements and tax computation, filing of profits and personal tax returns, and responding to IRD enquiries.

Requirements

Degree/diploma in Accounting or related discipline;
Student member/member of HKICPA or other recognisable professional accounting bodies;
Ability to work independently and deal with competing deadlines;
Excellent analytical, interpersonal and communication skills;
At least 5 years working experience;
Experience in dealing with foreign clients is an advantage;
Knowledge of accounting software (especially MYOB and Xero) will be advantageous;
Proficient in MS Word, Excel and Chinese Word Processing;
Good command in written and spoken English and Chinese. Fluency in Putonghua is a plus.

We invite high-caliber candidates who are looking for advancement in his/her professional career to apply. We offer the successful candidate an attractive remuneration package including annual leave, examination leave, study leave and double pay. Our company works 5 days per week.

Please apply by sending e-mail to recruit@ sejong.com.hk.
Please contact 2970 7500 for inquiries.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Assistant

The Hong Kong Investment Funds Association (“HKIFA”) is a non-profit-making organization that represents the fund management industry in Hong Kong.  www.hkifa.org.hk.  We aim to recruit a high caliber candidate who will play a key role in the following areas.

Responsibilities:

The main responsibilities include, amongst others:

l  Provide support to meetings (including planning, preparing agendas/papers, managing meeting logistics, taking minutes/notes, and following up to implement the decisions reached at meetings);

l  Perform desk-top research related to specific topics, and prepare papers/reports accordingly;

l  Liaise with member firms to solicit and collate inputs to prepare consultation responses and prepare reports/white papers for submission to the authorities/regulators or other stakeholder groups;

l  Assist in website/social media maintenance, and prepare materials for posting; and

l  Assist in administrative/ad hoc tasks as required.

Attributes and qualities:

l  University graduate;

l Experience in capital markets and ESG a plus;  

l  Strong writing skills – both English and Chinese;

l  Proactive, detail-oriented and be able to take on multi-tasks; and

l  Have excellent PC skills.

Interested parties please email to Hong Kong Investment Funds Association
